## Context

Transformers.js supports many vision-language models (Florence-2, LLaVA, Qwen2-VL, etc.) via `AutoModelForImageTextToText` in `src/models.js`, but there is no corresponding pipeline class. This plan adds `ImageTextToTextPipeline` so users can call `pipeline('image-text-to-text', model_id)` and run multimodal inference with an image + text prompt.

`AutoModelForImageTextToText` already exists and is fully exported. The only file that needs changes is **`src/pipelines.js`**.

---

## Critical File

- **`src/pipelines.js`** — only file to modify (all 4 changes below are in this file)

---

## Key References Found in Codebase

| Reference | Location |
|---|---|
| `ImageToTextPipeline` | lines 1920–2005 — handles image → generated text |
| `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` | lines 2732–2779 — handles image + text → generated text |
| `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` typedef | lines ~210–216 — already covers tokenizer + processor |
| `SUPPORTED_TASKS` object | lines 3096–3390 |
| `"image-to-text"` entry in SUPPORTED_TASKS | lines 3244–3255 |
| `"document-question-answering"` entry | lines 3330–3341 |
| `pipeline()` factory JSDoc | lines ~3414–3445 |
| `prepareImages()` helper | used in both reference pipelines |
| `AutoModelForImageTextToText` import | **NOT yet imported** in pipelines.js |

---

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1 — Add import for `AutoModelForImageTextToText`

In the imports block (around line 40), add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the existing destructured import from `'./models.js'`:

```js
